19 I HAVE OTHER QUESTIONS ABOUT THIS FORM. WHAT SHOULD I DO? THIS
20 FORM IS DESIGNED TO FIT SOME BUT NOT ALL SITUATIONS. IF YOU HAVE OTHER
21 QUESTIONS, CONSULT A LAWYER.”.
22 14–1013.
23 (A) (1) ON THE DEATH OF A TRANSFEROR, A BENEFICIARY OR THE
24 BENEFICIARIES OF A TRANSFER–ON–DEATH DEED MAY RECORD NOTICE OF THE
25 DEATH OF A TRANSFEROR IN THE LAND RECORDS OF THE COUNTY IN WHICH THE
26 PROPERTY IS LOCATED.
27 (2) NOTICE OF THE DEATH OF THE TRANSFEROR IS NOT REQUIRED
28 TO EFFECTUATE THE TRANSFER OF THE PROPERTY, WHICH IS DEEMED TO HAVE
29 OCCURRED AT THE DEATH OF THE TRANSFEROR.
30 (3) THE CLERK OF THE COURT SHALL FORWARD NOTIFICATION OF
31 THE DEATH OF A TRANSFEROR TO THE MARYLAND STATE DEPARTMENT OF
32 ASSESSMENTS AND TAXATION IN THE SAME MANNER AS A DEED OR A LEASE.

HOUSE BILL 738 29
1 (B) THE FOLLOWING FORM MAY BE USED AND RECORDED UNDER
2 SUBSECTION (A) OF THIS SECTION TO PROVIDE NOTICE OF THE DEATH OF A
3 TRANSFEROR:
