15 14–1014.
16 THIS SUBTITLE MODIFIES, LIMITS, AND SUPERSEDES THE FEDERAL
17 ELECTRONIC SIGNATURES IN GLOBAL AND NATIONAL COMMERCE ACT, 15 U.S.C.
18 SECTION 7001, ET SEQ., BUT DOES NOT MODIFY, LIMIT, OR SUPERSEDE SECTION
19 101(C) OF THAT ACT, 15 U.S.C. SECTION 7001(C), OR AUTHORIZE ELECTRONIC
20 DELIVERY OF ANY OF THE NOTICES DESCRIBED IN SECTION 103(B) OF THAT ACT, 15
21 U.S.C. SECTION 7003(B).
22 Article – Tax – Property
23 12–108.
24 (II) A REAL PROPERTY TRANSFER–ON–DEATH DEED UNDER TITLE 14 OF
25 THE REAL PROPERTY ARTICLE IS NOT SUBJECT TO RECORDATION TAX IF THE
26 PROPERTY IS A PRIMARY RESIDENCE OR A SECONDARY RESIDENCE OF THE
27 TRANSFEROR.
28 13–207.
29 (a) An instrument of writing is not subject to transfer tax to the same extent that
30 it is not subject to recordation tax under:

32 HOUSE BILL 738
1 (25) § 12–108(gg) of this article (Transfer of principal residence surrendered
2 in bankruptcy); [or]
3 (26) § 12–108(hh) of this article (Transfer of real property within the Pimlico
4 racing facility site, Pimlico site, Bowie Race Course Training Center property, or training
5 facility site); OR
6 (27) § 12–108(II) OF THIS ARTICLE (REAL PROPERTY
7 TRANSFER–ON–DEATH DEED).
8 13–414.
9 AN INSTRUMENT OF WRITING THAT IS EXEMPT FROM RECORDATION TAX
10 UNDER § 12–108(II) OF THIS ARTICLE (REAL PROPERTY TRANSFER–ON–DEATH
11 DEED) IS NOT SUBJECT TO COUNTY TRANSFER TAX.
12 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall be interpreted
13 and enforced by a court in accordance with existing law governing life estates with powers
14 of alienation, to the extent practicable and so long as the interpretation and enforcement
15 does not conflict with the uniform application of the Uniform Real Property Transfer on
16 Death Act promulgated by the Uniform Law Commission.
17 SECTION 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall apply to a
18 transfer–on–death deed that was made before, on, or after the effective date of this Act by
19 a transferor who dies on or after the effective date of this Act.
20 SECTION 4. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
21 October 1, 2026.
Approved:
